Comments:       Advanced Linux Sound Architecture config and test files,
                which may only be required for legacy/exotic hardware
                ----------
                If loading alsa-config followed by alsa doesn't work, try:
                $ sudo /usr/local/etc/init.d/alsasound start
		If adding this command to bootlocal.sh, you may need
		to precede it with the sleep command for it to be effective.
                ----------
                To test sound, use alsamixer to un-mute the master and then:
                $ speaker-test [-Ddefault:1] -c2 -t wav -l1
                [change default to suit multiple cards]
